---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="RevOps & Fractional CRO Services | Fixed-Fee Engagements | OrangeCore Group"
  description="Productized RevOps and fractional CRO services for B2B SaaS and fintech. Foundation audit from $5,500. Full HubSpot buildout from $14,500. No hourly billing."
>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hc1"></div><div class="hc2"></div>
    <div class="container hero-inner">
      <div class="eyebrow hero-ey">Productized RevOps Services</div>
      <h1>RevOps and Fractional CRO Services — Fixed Scope, Fixed Price</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Fixed scope. Fixed price. Real deliverables — not a slide deck and an open-ended retainer. You'll know exactly what you're getting before anything gets signed.</p>
      <div class="hero-stats">
        <div class="stat"><span class="stat-num">14</span><span class="stat-label">days avg. delivery</span></div>
        <div class="stat"><span class="stat-num">4</span><span class="stat-label">engagement options</span></div>
        <div class="stat"><span class="stat-num">$0</span><span class="stat-label">hourly billing</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="position-strip fade-in">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Why this isn't traditional fractional consulting</p>
      <div class="compare-grid">
        <div class="compare-col compare-old">
          <h3>Traditional fractional CRO/RevOps</h3>
          <div class="compare-item"><span>—</span><span>Hourly or day-rate billing. Budget creep is a feature, not a bug.</span></div>
          <div class="compare-item"><span>—</span><span>Weeks of "discovery" before anything is actually built.</span></div>
          <div class="compare-item"><span>—</span><span>You own the relationship. They own the knowledge. When they leave, so does it.</span></div>
          <div class="compare-item"><span>—</span><span>Vague deliverables. "Strategic guidance." Hard to measure ROI.</span></div>
          <div class="compare-item"><span>—</span><span>Scope expands every month. Engagement never ends.</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="compare-col compare-new">
          <h3>OrangeCore productized service</h3>
          <div class="compare-item"><span class="chk">✓</span><span>Flat fee. You know the number before we start. No surprises.</span></div>
          <div class="compare-item"><span class="chk">✓</span><span>Structured intake on day one. Building starts in week one.</span></div>
          <div class="compare-item"><span class="chk">✓</span><span>Everything documented and handed off. It's yours when we're done.</span></div>
          <div class="compare-item"><span class="chk">✓</span><span>Specific deliverables. You'll know exactly what you're getting before you sign.</span></div>
          <div class="compare-item"><span class="chk">✓</span><span>Defined end date. Retainer is optional — never required.</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header fade-in">
        <p class="eyebrow">Service tiers</p>
        <h2>Pick where you actually are right now.</h2>
        <p>Every tier has a defined scope and a defined end. You'll know exactly what you're getting before you sign anything.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="pricing-grid">
        <div class="pricing-card card-hover fade-in" id="foundation">
          <div class="card-top">
            <p class="card-tier">Tier 1</p>
            <h2 class="card-name">Foundation</h2>
            <p class="card-tagline">Something's off and you can feel it — but nobody can agree on what. This tells you exactly what's broken and what to do about it.</p>
            <div class="price-block"><span class="price-main">$5,500</span></div>
            <p class="price-note">One-time. Flat.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <div class="timeline-pill">Delivered in 10 business days</div>
            <p class="deliv-label">What you get</p>
            <ul class="check-list">
              <li>Full RevOps audit — pipeline, CRM, ICP definition, handoff process</li>
              <li>Gap analysis with prioritized fix list (what to do first, what to ignore)</li>
              <li>90-day RevOps roadmap, ready to execute</li>
              <li>HubSpot / CRM health scorecard</li>
              <li>60-min readout call + Q&A</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="deliv-label">Best for</p>
            <p class="best-for">Growth-stage teams that have never had a real RevOps foundation. Also the right move before committing to a full Build — start here if you're not 100% sure what's broken.</p>
            <a href="/contact/" class="btn-outline card-cta">Get started</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pricing-card pricing-card--featured card-hover fade-in" id="operate">
          <div class="featured-badge">Most popular</div>
          <div class="card-top">
            <p class="card-tier">Ongoing</p>
            <h2 class="card-name">Operate</h2>
            <p class="card-tagline">You need a CRO in the room without the full-time price tag. Every month has defined deliverables — not a standing check-in call you dread scheduling.</p>
            <div class="price-block"><span class="price-main">$7,500</span><span class="price-suffix">/mo</span></div>
            <p class="price-note">3-month minimum. Deliverables locked in at kickoff.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <div class="timeline-pill">Starts within 5 business days</div>
            <p class="deliv-label">Monthly deliverables (defined at kickoff)</p>
            <ul class="check-list">
              <li>Monthly pipeline review + forecast call with leadership</li>
              <li>One major deliverable per month (playbook, process, campaign framework)</li>
              <li>Ongoing CRM management and data hygiene</li>
              <li>Sales team coaching sessions (bi-weekly)</li>
              <li>Async Slack access for real-time questions</li>
              <li>Monthly performance report with next-month priorities</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="deliv-label">Best for</p>
            <p class="best-for">Funded companies without a full-time CRO or VP Sales. Works especially well after a Build engagement — keep the momentum going without adding headcount.</p>
            <p class="ai-note">Every Operate engagement is AI-augmented. Faster turnaround, consistent output, higher-quality analysis every month.</p>
            <a href="/contact/" class="btn-primary card-cta">Get started</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pricing-card card-hover fade-in" id="build">
          <div class="card-top">
            <p class="card-tier">Project</p>
            <h2 class="card-name">Build</h2>
            <p class="card-tagline">The full engagement. We go in, build it right, hand it off clean. No loose ends, no "let's revisit next quarter."</p>
            <div class="price-block"><span class="price-main">$14,500</span></div>
            <p class="price-note">One-time. Flat. Includes 30 days of support post-delivery.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <div class="timeline-pill">Delivered in 3–4 weeks</div>
            <p class="deliv-label">Everything in Foundation, plus</p>
            <ul class="check-list">
              <li>Full CRM buildout or cleanup (HubSpot, Salesforce)</li>
              <li>ICP definition + segmentation framework</li>
              <li>Pipeline stages built and configured with entry/exit criteria</li>
              <li>Sales playbook (talk tracks, objection handling, discovery framework)</li>
              <li>Reporting dashboard — metrics that actually mean something</li>
              <li>Marketing-to-sales handoff process, documented and implemented</li>
              <li>30-day Slack support post-delivery</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="deliv-label">Best for</p>
            <p class="best-for">Series A/B companies that have outgrown whatever they cobbled together early on. Also strong for teams prepping to hire a CRO — hand them something that doesn't embarrass anyone.</p>
            <a href="/contact/" class="btn-outline card-cta">Get started</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="enterprise-row card-hover fade-in">
        <div>
          <p class="card-tier">Custom Enterprise</p>
          <h3 class="enterprise-name">Complex environment? Let's scope it together.</h3>
          <p class="enterprise-desc">Multi-location orgs, legacy CRM migrations, enterprise procurement environments, or fintech/payments companies with compliance-adjacent sales cycles. If it doesn't fit neatly into one of the tiers above, this is the conversation to have.</p>
          <div class="enterprise-checks">
            <span>✓ Custom scope defined upfront</span>
            <span>✓ Flat-fee or milestone billing</span>
            <span>✓ Payments &amp; fintech experience available</span>
            <span>✓ SDVOSB certified — qualifies for set-aside contracts</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="enterprise-cta-block">
          <p class="enterprise-price">Starts at $25K</p>
          <p class="price-note" style="margin-bottom:1rem;">Scoped per engagement</p>
          <a href="/contact/" class="btn-outline">Let's talk scope</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="addons-section fade-in">
        <div class="section-header">
          <p class="eyebrow">Add-ons</p>
          <h2>Need something specific?</h2>
          <p>These can be added to any tier or purchased standalone.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="addons-grid">
          <div class="addon-card card-hover"><p class="addon-name">HubSpot Migration</p><p class="addon-desc">Full migration from another CRM or a legacy HubSpot setup. Clean data import, custom properties, workflows rebuilt.</p><p class="addon-price">$4,500</p></div>
          <div class="addon-card card-hover"><p class="addon-name">GTM Strategy Sprint</p><p class="addon-desc">2-week focused engagement to define or sharpen go-to-market motion — ICP, positioning, channel prioritization, outbound strategy.</p><p class="addon-price">$5,500</p></div>
          <div class="addon-card card-hover"><p class="addon-name">Board / Investor Prep</p><p class="addon-desc">Pipeline narrative, revenue forecast model, and GTM slide package built for your next board meeting or fundraise conversation.</p><p class="addon-price">$2,000</p></div>
          <div class="addon-card card-hover"><p class="addon-name">Comp Plan Design</p><p class="addon-desc">Sales compensation structure for AEs, SDRs, and CS. Quota modeling, accelerators, and spiff design included.</p><p class="addon-price">$3,000</p></div>
          <div class="addon-card card-hover"><p class="addon-name">RevOps Tech Stack Audit</p><p class="addon-desc">Full review of your current tool stack — what to keep, what to cut, what's missing. Includes vendor comparison where relevant.</p><p class="addon-price">$2,500</p></div>
          <div class="addon-card card-hover"><p class="addon-name">Payments / Fintech Vertical Pack</p><p class="addon-desc">Playbook and ICP framework built specifically for payments, BNPL, or fintech — with MCC, interchange, and enterprise procurement context baked in.</p><p class="addon-price">$3,500</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="fit-dark fade-in">
        <div class="fit-col fit-yes">
          <h3>This is for you if...</h3>
          <div class="fit-item"><span>✓</span><span>Revenue is inconsistent — good months, bad months, no real explanation for either.</span></div>
          <div class="fit-item"><span>✓</span><span>Your CRM is a graveyard. The team knows it's wrong so they've stopped using it.</span></div>
          <div class="fit-item"><span>✓</span><span>Sales and marketing can't agree on what a qualified lead looks like.</span></div>
          <div class="fit-item"><span>✓</span><span>You're heading into a board meeting or a fundraise and the pipeline story isn't airtight.</span></div>
          <div class="fit-item"><span>✓</span><span>You need CRO-level thinking but $250K in salary isn't happening right now.</span></div>
          <div class="fit-item"><span>✓</span><span>You're in fintech, payments, BNPL, or B2B SaaS and tired of generalists who don't know the space.</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="fit-col fit-no">
          <h3>This probably isn't for you if...</h3>
          <div class="fit-item fi-no"><span>—</span><span>You're pre-revenue and still figuring out if anyone wants what you're selling. Fix that first.</span></div>
          <div class="fit-item fi-no"><span>—</span><span>You want someone to sit in meetings and give general advice. That's not a service, that's a habit.</span></div>
          <div class="fit-item fi-no"><span>—</span><span>You need a day-to-day sales manager. That's a hire, not a consultant.</span></div>
          <div class="fit-item fi-no"><span>—</span><span>You're not comfortable letting someone look at the real numbers. This only works with full visibility.</span></div>
          <div class="fit-item fi-no"><span>—</span><span>You want a rolling retainer with no defined output. Plenty of firms will take that money — we're not one of them.</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-section fade-in">
        <div class="section-header">
          <p class="eyebrow">Common questions</p>
          <h2>Stuff people actually ask.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-grid">
          <div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-q">What if we need more than what's in the scope?</p><p class="faq-a">Scope is defined at kickoff so there are no surprises. If something new comes up that's genuinely outside the original scope, we'll discuss it — but I'm not going to nickel-and-dime you on small things.</p></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-q">Do you work in our CRM or build a new one?</p><p class="faq-a">Both, depending on what makes sense. I work in HubSpot, Salesforce, or Pipedrive. If your current setup is beyond saving, I'll tell you that upfront — not three weeks in.</p></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-q">What's the payment structure?</p><p class="faq-a">50% upfront, 50% on delivery for Foundation and Build. Operate is billed monthly at the start of each month.</p></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-q">Can we start with Foundation and upgrade to Build?</p><p class="faq-a">Yes — and that's actually a common path. The Foundation fee applies toward a Build engagement if you move within 30 days of delivery.</p></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-q">Do you work with early-stage companies?</p><p class="faq-a">The sweet spot is post-Series A, but I've worked with bootstrapped companies with strong revenue too. If you're still figuring out product-market fit, Foundation might be premature.</p></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-q">What's your payments and fintech experience?</p><p class="faq-a">It runs deep — interchange economics, tokenization, BNPL infrastructure, enterprise procurement in financial services. Past clients include Verifone and Bread Financial. It's not a talking point, it's actual background.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="footer-cta-banner fade-in">
        <h2>Not sure where you fit?</h2>
        <p>30 minutes. No pitch deck, no pressure. We'll figure out together if this makes sense — and if it doesn't, I'll tell you that too. Based in Plano, TX, serving DFW and clients nationwide.</p>
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn-primary">Book a discovery call</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
.hero{background:var(--charcoal);padding:5rem 0 4rem;position:relative;overflow:hidden;text-align:center;}
.hc1,.hc2{position:absolute;border-radius:50%;background:var(--orange);pointer-events:none;}
.hc1{width:300px;height:300px;top:-60px;right:-60px;opacity:0.07;}
.hc2{width:200px;height:200px;bottom:-80px;left:-40px;opacity:0.05;}
.hero-inner{position:relative;z-index:1;}
.hero-ey{color:var(--orange);border:1px solid rgba(232,97,10,0.4);padding:4px 14px;border-radius:2px;}
.hero h1{font-size:clamp(2rem,5vw,3.4rem);font-weight:700;color:#fff;line-height:1.12;letter-spacing:-0.03em;max-width:800px;margin:1rem auto 1.25rem;}
.hero-sub{font-size:17px;color:#9A9590;max-width:560px;margin:0 auto 2.5rem;font-weight:300;line-height:1.7;}
.hero-stats{display:flex;justify-content:center;gap:3rem;padding-top:2rem;border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);flex-wrap:wrap;}
.stat{text-align:center;}.stat-num{font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:2rem;font-weight:700;color:#fff;display:block;}
.stat-label{font-size:12px;color:#6E6A65;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;}
.position-strip{background:var(--orange-light);border-top:1px solid var(--orange-mid);border-bottom:1px solid var(--orange-mid);padding:2.5rem 0;}
.compare-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:1.5rem;margin-top:1.25rem;}
.compare-col h3{font-family:var(--font-sans);font-size:13px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:0.06em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:1rem;padding-bottom:0.5rem;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);}
.compare-old h3{color:var(--mid-gray);}.compare-new h3{color:var(--green);}
.compare-item{display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:10px;margin-bottom:0.75rem;font-size:14px;line-height:1.5;}
.compare-item span:first-child{flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px;}
.compare-old .compare-item{color:#7A7570;}.compare-new .compare-item{color:var(--charcoal);}
.chk{color:var(--green);}
.pricing-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:1.25rem;align-items:start;margin-bottom:2rem;}
.pricing-card{background:var(--white);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:6px;overflow:hidden;}
.pricing-card--featured{border:2px solid var(--orange);position:relative;}
.featured-badge{position:absolute;top:-1px;right:20px;background:var(--orange);color:#fff;font-size:10px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:4px 12px;border-radius:0 0 4px 4px;}
.card-top{padding:1.75rem 1.75rem 1.5rem;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);}
.card-tier{font-size:11px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mid-gray);margin-bottom:0.4rem;}
.card-name{font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--charcoal);margin-bottom:0.5rem;letter-spacing:-0.02em;}
.card-tagline{font-size:13px;color:var(--mid-gray);line-height:1.5;margin-bottom:1.25rem;}
.price-block{display:flex;align-items:baseline;gap:4px;}
.price-main{font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:2.4rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--charcoal);letter-spacing:-0.03em;}
.price-suffix{font-size:1.1rem;color:var(--mid-gray);font-weight:400;}
.price-note{font-size:12px;color:var(--mid-gray);margin-top:4px;}
.card-body{padding:1.5rem 1.75rem 1.75rem;}
.timeline-pill{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;font-size:12px;color:var(--mid-gray);margin-bottom:1.25rem;}
.timeline-pill::before{content:'';display:block;width:6px;height:6px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--orange);flex-shrink:0;}
.deliv-label{font-size:11px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mid-gray);margin:1.25rem 0 0.6rem;}
.best-for{font-size:13px;color:var(--mid-gray);line-height:1.5;margin-bottom:1.25rem;}
.ai-note{font-size:12px;color:var(--orange);background:var(--orange-light);border-radius:4px;padding:10px 12px;margin-bottom:1.25rem;line-height:1.5;}
.card-cta{width:100%;text-align:center;display:block;margin-top:0.5rem;}
.enterprise-row{background:var(--white);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:6px;padding:2rem;margin-bottom:4rem;display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr auto;gap:2rem;align-items:center;}
.enterprise-name{font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:1.4rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--charcoal);letter-spacing:-0.02em;margin:0.4rem 0 0.5rem;}
.enterprise-desc{font-size:13.5px;color:var(--mid-gray);line-height:1.6;max-width:620px;}
.enterprise-checks{display:flex;gap:1.5rem;margin-top:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;}
.enterprise-checks span{font-size:12px;color:var(--mid-gray);}
.enterprise-price{font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:1.1rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--charcoal);margin-bottom:4px;}
.enterprise-cta-block{text-align:center;min-width:160px;}
.addons-section{margin-bottom:4rem;}
.addons-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:1rem;}
.addon-card{background:var(--white);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:6px;padding:1.25rem;}
.addon-name{font-size:14px;font-weight:500;color:var(--charcoal);margin-bottom:4px;}
.addon-desc{font-size:12px;color:var(--mid-gray);line-height:1.5;margin-bottom:0.75rem;}
.addon-price{font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:1.1rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--orange);}
.fit-dark{background:var(--charcoal);border-radius:8px;padding:2.5rem;margin-bottom:4rem;display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:2.5rem;}
.fit-col h3{font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:1.2rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:1rem;}
.fit-yes h3{color:#4DC994;}.fit-no h3{color:#6E6A65;}
.fit-item{display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:10px;font-size:13.5px;padding:7px 0;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);line-height:1.45;color:#C8C4BF;}
.fit-item:last-child{border-bottom:none;}
.fit-item span:first-child{flex-shrink:0;font-size:13px;margin-top:1px;}
.fit-yes .fit-item span:first-child{color:#4DC994;}
.fi-no{color:#5A5653;}.fi-no span:first-child{color:#4A4744;}
.faq-section{margin-bottom:4rem;}
@media(max-width:768px){.pricing-grid,.compare-grid,.addons-grid,.fit-dark{grid-template-columns:1fr;}.enterprise-row{grid-template-columns:1fr;}.enterprise-cta-block{text-align:left;}}
</style>
